@node Introduction "AquaQuiet v1.1 Documentation"

Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~
This is a replacement for the internal Q command, to toggle whether a node
is quiet (not visible to others) or not. The bad thing about the internal
Q command is that it never displays anything! AquaQuiet shows if the node
was made quiet or if the "quietness" was turned off. You can define the
texts to be shown yourself. Also, if the user hasn't got access to make
the node quiet the internal Q command says nothing! He has to use WHO to
check if it worked or not. AquaQuiet on the other hand displays "Commands
requires higher access."
@endnode

@node Requirements "AquaQuiet v1.1 Documentation"

Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~
- An Amiga with OS 2.0 or higher.

- AmiExpress, SigmaExpress or any compatible program.
@endnode

@node Installation "AquaQuiet v1.1 Documentation"

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Installation is very easy. You can put the door anywhere, for example in
'Doors:'. It is an XIM type door. A command icon for AmiExpress 3.0+,
'Q.info', is provided. Put it in your 'BBSCmd' drawer.

For AmiExpress 2.xx and SigmaExpress, insert this line in your BBS.CMD:
---- Cut here --------------------------------
*Q        XM001Doors:AquaQuiet
------ Cut here ------------------------------

Note that the door access can be set to 1 (the lowest possible), because
AquaQuiet checks if the user has access to make the node quiet, which in
/X 3.0+ is determined by the presence of 'ACS.QUIET_NODE' in the user's
access icon.

The default text shown when a node is made quiet is "Quiet On". If you
want something else to be shown, write that in 'ENV:AquaQuiet.OnText'. The
default text for making a node NOT quiet is "Quiet Off". If you want
something else to be shown, write that in 'ENV:AquaQuiet.OffText'. Put
these two files in 'ENVARC:' as well, so that they are always copied to
'ENV:' at reboot.

AquaQuiet is "pure" and is therefore perfectly safe to make resident.
@endnode

@node History "AquaQuiet v1.1 Documentation"

History
~~~~~~~

1.0  (09-17-94) First release version.


1.1  (01-28-95) Second release. Version 1.0 could hang the node,
