@node AquaSettings "AquaQuiet v1.1 Documentation"

Note about AquaSettings
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
First of all, I'm glad so many boards are using AquaSettings! Just a few
days after release and suddenly it's installed on every other board! Cool!

But it seems I made a little mistake in the AquaSettings v1.0 archive..
In the provided configuration icon 'AquaSettings.info', the 'CMD.1'
tooltype was set to 'W'. It SHOULD have been 'W_INTERNAL'. This only goes
for AmiExpress 3.xx/4.xx. The icon was correct for SigmaExpress and
AmiExpress 2.xx. I did write about that in the doc, but there I assumed
'CMD.1' was 'W_INTERNAL' from the beginning.

So what's the difference? Well, when you start AquaSettings you get a menu
of different configuration stuff. The first entry is "Basic settings", or
whatever you name it, i.e. it starts the internal W command. But if
'CMD.1=W' then the door won't be able to return to the menu again. That's
because of a limitation in AmiExpress/S-Express which doesn't let any door
run an internal command (with the same name as a door), without quitting
the door first. But the W_INTERNAL command is a way around this. If you
use 'CMD.1=W_INTERNAL' with AmiExpress 3.xx/4.xx, then "Basic settings"
will behave like all the other menu entries: you will be taken back to the
AquaSettings menu afterwards.

I haven't seen it changed on any board, so what I have learnt from this is
that the contents of provided configuration files are very important, and
that most sysops don't bother to read the doc entirely and check the
configuration, which is a bit unfortunate.

  .------------------------------------------------------------------.
  | If you're running AmiExpress 3.xx/4.xx, change 'CMD.1=W' to      |
  | 'CMD.1=W_INTERNAL' in 'Doors:AquaSettings/AquaSettings.info',    |
  | and make sure you have copied 'W_INTERNAL.info' from the archive |
  | (OTL-SE10.LHA) to your 'BBSCmd' drawer (NOT 'SYSCmd').           |
  `------------------------------------------------------------------'
@endnode

